#
# fitfluxes 0 1 1 2:160,4:250,6:350,7:500 1:0.2,1:0.1,1:0.1,1:0.1 thinbody 0:1,0:1,2:0 470 10 0.01 California.sw.sources.ok.cat +verb2
#
# Input catalog: California.sw.sources.ok.cat
#  Output files: thin.California.sw.sources.ok.00.*
#
# Selected sources: ... global significance > 1
# Selected sources: ....... global goodness > 1
#
#  Wavebands for SED fitting: 1.60E+02 2.50E+02 3.50E+02 5.00E+02
# Additional relative errors: 2.00E-01 1.00E-01 1.00E-01 1.00E-01
#
# Adopted dust-to-gas mass ratio and relative error: ... 1.00E-02 2.00E-01
# Adopted reference dust opacity and relative error: ... 1.00E+01 2.00E-01
# Adopted distance (pc) and relative error: ............ 4.70E+02 0.00E+00
#
# Fitting model: thinbody ~> Fnu = Bnu(T) kappa M D^-2
#
# 1st parameter ....... temperature: variable
# 2nd parameter ........ total mass: variable
# 3rd parameter ..... opacity slope: constant
# 4th parameter .......... distance: constant
#____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
#
# TABULATED QUANTITIES:
#
#  1 NO .......... Input catalog source or image pixel number ...................
#  2 XCO_P ....... X-coordinate of current source or pixel ...................... pixels
#  3 YCO_P ....... Y-coordinate of current source or pixel ...................... pixels
#  4 SIG_GLOB .... Global significance or part of all pixels to fit .............
#  5 GOOD ........ Global goodness or number of equal parts of pixels ...........
#  6 DUST_TEMP ... Derived dust temperature of source or pixel .................. K
#  7 TEMP_ERRO ... Uncertainty of derived temperature ........................... K
#  8 TOTL_MASS ... Derived total mass (gas+dust) of source ...................... Msun
#  9 MASS_ERRO ... Uncertainty of derived mass from SED fitting ................. Msun
# 10 MASS_ERRT ... Total mass uncertainty (incl. distance opacity dust/gas) ..... Msun
# 11 BOLO_LUMI ... Derived bolometric luminosity ................................ Lsun
# 12 LUMI_ERRO ... Uncertainty of derived luminosity ............................ Lsun
# 13 SLD_ANGLE ... Derived solid angle (diameter) ............................... arcsec
# 14 ANGL_ERRO ... Uncertainty of derived solid angle ........................... arcsec
